cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on the task of adversarial attacks in visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the adaptation of existing attack methods and proposes a new attack method, which involves optimization-based techniques and incremental perturbations, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the proposed method is conducted on various datasets, which involves the analysis of multimedia content (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of generating imperceptible perturbations, which is related to the field of computer security (cs.CR).
